snippet.textDisplay: I've eaten a lot of hot sauce and I love it. I've made my own sauce and I think the difference between the in your face sledgehammer to the mouth hot sauce and the creeper is a combination of the type of pepper and how it's prepared. Fermented sauces seem to creep a lot more and finish a lot hotter. Vinegar sauces seem to be more of the first type. Quickly hot and quickly gone. Different peppers also seem to hit differently.
